{{Infobox journal | title = Management Science | cover = Management Sciense May 2011 cover.gif | editor = David Simchi-Levi | discipline = [[Management]] | abbreviation = Manag. Sci. | publisher = [[Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences]] | country = United States | frequency = Monthly | history = 1954-present | openaccess = | impact = 2.822 | impact-year = 2016 | website = http://pubsonline.informs.org/journal/mnsc | link1 = http://pubsonline.informs.org/toc/mnsc/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://pubsonline.informs.org/loi/mnsc | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = 00251909 | ISSN = 0025-1909 | eISSN = 1526-5501 | CODEN = MSCIAM | LCCN = 56021107 | OCLC = 01641131 }}
'''''Management Science''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] that covers research on all aspects of [[management]] related to [[Strategic management|strategy]], [[entrepreneurship]], innovation, [[information technology]], and organizations as well as all functional areas of [[business]], such as [[accounting]], [[finance]], [[marketing]], and [[Operations research|operations]]. It is published by the [[Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences]] and was established in 1954 by the Institute's precursor, The Institute of Management Sciences. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', the journal has an [[impact factor]] of 2.822.<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2016 |chapter=Management Science |title=2016 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Science |series=[[Web of Science]] |postscript=.}}</ref>
== History == On December 1, 1953 at the founding meeting at Columbia University, [[The Institute of Management Sciences]] was voted into existence and William Cooper was elected as the first president. Establishment of a journal, to be called ''Management Science'', was made the first order of business. Almost immediately after the meeting, Cooper recruited [[C. West Churchman]] to be the founding editor. Cooper, Churchman, and Abe Charnes then wrote the policy statement for the journal. Within weeks Churchman had assembled an [[editorial board]] and had the first issue ready for distribution at the first membership meeting of the institute in October 1954.
C. West Churchman quickly built ''Management Science'', both in size and reputation. By 1960 when he stepped down as editor, the journal was publishing almost twice as many papers per year as it had in the first volume. True to his vision, Churchman published papers representing a wide range of disciplines, from optimization, inventory, and [[game theory]] to [[management psychology]], leadership, and the [[epistemology of science]].<ref> https://www.informs.org/content/download/166515/1701945/file/Churchman%20Tribute.pdf </ref>{{third-party-inline|date=October 2014}}
== Editors-in-chief == The following persons are, or have been, [[editors-in-chief]]: * 2018–2020: David Simchi-Levi * 2014–2018: [[Teck-Hua Ho]] * 2009–2014: Gérard Cachon * 2003–2008: Wallace Hopp * 1997–2002: Hau L. Lee * 1993–1997: Gabriel R. Bitran * 1983–1990: Donald G. Morrison * 1968–1983: Martin K. Starr * 1960–1967: Robert M. Thrall * 1954–1960: [[C. West Churchman]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pubsonline.informs.org/page/mnsc/stats-history |title=History |work=Management Science |publisher=[[Institute for Operations Research and the Management Sciences]] |accessdate=18 October 2014}}</ref>
== Notable papers == According to [[Google Scholar]], the following three papers have been cited most frequently:<ref name=GS>{{cite web|url=https://scholar.google.com/ |title=Google Scholar |publisher=[[Google Scholar|Google]] |accessdate=2015-04-27 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090903014320/https://scholar.google.com/ |archivedate=2009-09-03 |df= }}</ref> * {{cite journal |doi=10.1287/mnsc.9.2.277 |title=A Simplified Model for Portfolio Analysis |journal=Management Science |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages=277 |year=1963 |last1=Sharpe |first1=William F.}} * {{cite journal |doi=10.1287/mnsc.1040.0270 |title=Games with Incomplete Information Played by "Bayesian" Players, I–III: Part I. The Basic Model& |journal=Management Science |volume=50 |issue=12_supplement |pages=1804 |year=1967 |last1=Harsanyi |first1=John C.}} * {{cite journal |doi=10.1287/mnsc.15.5.215 |title=A New Product Growth for Model Consumer Durables |journal=Management Science |volume=15 |issue=5 |pages=215 |year=1969 |last1=Bass |first1=Frank M.}}
